<p>Will the 2nd line of the following code</p>  <pre><code>int bar; int foo = bar * 3 * 5; </code></pre>  <p>be optimized to</p>  <pre><code>int bar; int foo = bar * 15; </code></pre>  <p>Or even more:</p>  <pre><code>int foo = 3 * bar * 5; </code></pre>  <p>can be optimized?</p>  <p>The purpose is actually to ask if I can just write</p>  <pre><code>int foo = bar * 3 * 5; </code></pre>  <p>instead of</p>  <pre><code>int foo = bar * (3 * 5); </code></pre>  <p>to save the parentheses. (and the relieve the need to manually manipulate those constant ordering => and in many case grouping constants with related variables are more meaningful rather than grouping constants for optimization)</p>